imt: sky be.dark like cavern earth be.dark like cave
src: ntuj tsaus li qhov.paj teb tsaus li qhov.tsua.
trs: \sqt{The sky was as dark as a cavern, the earth as dark as a cave.}\footnote{The expression \textit{qhov paj} (lit: ‘hole flower’) does not, by itself, mean ‘cavern’. However here, in combination with \textit{qhov tsua} ‘cave’ (lit: ‘hole rock’), it is probably functioning poetically to refer to limestone caves characterized by flower-like stalactite formations, more generally referred to as \textit{qhov tsua tawg paj} (lit: ‘hole rock bloom flower’) or \textit{qhov tsua paj kaub} (lit: ‘hole rock flower crust’) in Hmong.}
